Listen on VimeoOrenburg, a southern Russian city close to the Kazakhstan border, is home to Long Arm, AKA Georgii Kotunov. Starting out with DIY musical equipment built from Soviet phonographs, he's gone on to developed a baroque, semi-improvised technique informed by his study of jazz.The above clip shows Long Arm in the Ukrainian river port of Dnipropetrovsk , together with friend and percussionist Ruslan Gadzhimuradov, who’s from the Arctic settlement of Norilsk. Read more about both men here.• The Invisible Hands: New music from Egypt• Ringo Sheena – Netsuai Hakkaku-chu: New music from Japan